---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/ui/PageHeader.astro';
import Section from '../../components/ui/Section.astro';
import Grid from '../../components/ui/Grid.astro';
import Card from '../../components/ui/Card.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Bruce Denham | Adobe Award-Nominated Technical Writer & DX Engineer"
  description="Meet Bruce Denham: Adobe award-nominated Senior Technical Writer & Developer Experience Engineer with 30+ years transforming complex APIs into clear developer experiences at Adobe, TOPAZ, and Schlumberger."
  showBackLink={true}
  backLinkText="← Back to Home"
  backLinkHref="/"
  footerText="Want to collaborate? "
  footerLinkText="Let's connect on LinkedIn"
  footerLinkHref="https://linkedin.com/in/brucedenham/"
>
  <PageHeader primary="About" accent="Me" class="page-title" />

  <!-- Intro section with text and photo side-by-side -->
  <div class="intro-section animate-in animate-delay-100">
    <div class="intro-content">
      <p class="text-large lead">
        👋 Hey there! I'm Bruce and over the past 30+ years I've learned that great writing is about
        becoming your audience. When you become them, you experience all their pains and struggles.
        Then you can write your way out of it and help them avoid the same pain. Turns out most
        developers would rather maintain jQuery than read the docs. I get it. So I try to keep it
        simple. But simple is hard. It takes time that's not easy to find. Ultimately, if a
        sleep-deprived developer can't understand my docs at 2 am, my docs aren't good enough. I
        fail a lot. But I keep trying.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="intro-image">
      <img
        src="/images/bruce-denham-headshot.jpg"
        alt="Bruce Denham - Senior Technical Writer & Developer Experience Engineer"
        width="300"
        height="400"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <Section title="Recognition & Community Impact" class="animate-in animate-delay-200">
    <Grid variant="default" gap="medium">
      <Card title="🏆 Adobe Awards">
        <p>
          Nominated for both the Adobe Founders Award and Extreme Ownership Award for excellence in
          technical writing and developer experience innovation.
        </p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="🎤 International Speaking">
        <p>
          Presented PageBuilder best practices at Meet Magento Indonesia 2019, sharing insights with
          the international open-source community.
        </p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="⭐ Community Leadership">
        <p>
          Created the PageBuilder Examples repository: 106 GitHub stars, 78 forks—highest engagement
          in the PageBuilder ecosystem. I encouraged community involvement through an open Slack
          channel to help developers worldwide.
        </p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="📚 Mentoring & Education">
        <p>
          Passionate about lifting others through shared knowledge, actively mentoring aspiring
          technical writers and students at Southwestern University. I also love to help teams
          establish effective documentation practices.
        </p>
      </Card>
    </Grid>
  </Section>

  <Section title="My Journey" class="animate-in animate-delay-300">
    <Grid variant="single" gap="medium">
      <Card
        title="Adobe, Inc."
        featured={true}
        period="2018-now"
        role="Senior Technical Writer & Developer Experience Specialist"
      >
        <p>
          Leading documentation products across multiple teams at one of the world's premier
          creative software companies. I manage the Adobe Storefront Commerce documentation site,
          build interactive React apps for API demonstrations, and develop CLI tools that streamline
          developer workflows.
        </p>
        <p>
          My work includes everything from SDK documentation using Storybook 8 to custom Algolia
          search integrations that help developers find answers fast. I've been recognized by peers
          and leadership for creativity, UX expertise, and technical writing excellence.
        </p>
      </Card>

      <Card
        title="TOPAZ Technologies"
        period="2006-2018"
        role="Senior Product Designer / Developer Support"
      >
        <p>
          During my 12 years at TOPAZ, I evolved from visual designer to full-stack product
          strategist. I led comprehensive UI overhauls of legacy AngularJS applications, trained
          development teams on Angular Material best practices, and managed end-to-end product
          marketing strategies.
        </p>
        <p>
          This role taught me the importance of bridging the gap between technical capability and
          user needs— a philosophy that continues to drive my approach to developer experience
          today.
        </p>
      </Card>

      <Card
        title="Schlumberger"
        period="2000-2005"
        role="Senior Technical Writer / API Documentation Specialist"
      >
        <p>
          My foundation in technical writing was built in the oil & gas industry, where I wrote API
          documentation and training guides that enabled 100+ global developers to adopt complex
          systems quickly. I also built UI prototypes in C#/WinForms and integrated systems with SQL
          Server databases.
        </p>
        <p>
          This experience taught me that great documentation isn't just about explaining what
          something does—it's about understanding why someone would want to use it and removing
          every possible barrier to their success.
        </p>
      </Card>
    </Grid>
  </Section>

  <Section title="What I Bring to the Table" class="animate-in animate-delay-250">
    <Grid variant="default" gap="medium">
      <Card title="Technical Writing" ariaLabel="Technical Writing Skills">
        <ul>
          <li>API documentation that drives adoption</li>
          <li>Developer tutorials that simplify complex workflows</li>
          <li>Interactive playgrounds for hands-on learning</li>
          <li>Diátaxis documentation framework expertise</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Development & Tools" ariaLabel="Development and Tools Skills">
        <ul>
          <li>React 18+, Node.js, and modern JavaScript frameworks</li>
          <li>CLI tool development for productivity enhancement</li>
          <li>Git/GitHub workflows and automation</li>
          <li>Frontend development with responsive design</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Visual Communication" ariaLabel="Visual Communication Skills">
        <ul>
          <li>UI/UX design for developer tools</li>
          <li>Infographics that clarify technical concepts</li>
          <li>Animation and video for process explanation</li>
          <li>Visual design that balances beauty and usability</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Leadership & Strategy" ariaLabel="Leadership & Strategy Skills">
        <ul>
          <li>Cross-functional collaboration with UX, PM, and Engineering</li>
          <li>Developer advocacy and community building</li>
          <li>Remote team leadership and mentoring</li>
          <li>Product strategy aligned with user needs</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>
    </Grid>
  </Section>

  <Section title="My Philosophy" class="animate-in animate-delay-200">
    <Grid variant="default" gap="medium">
      <Card
        icon="🎯"
        title="I don't just write the docs"
        description="I build tools, craft interfaces, and create explanations that click. Understanding how things work from the inside makes all the difference in explaining them clearly."
        ariaLabel="I don't just write the docs"
      />

      <Card
        icon="💡"
        title="Spark 'aha' moments"
        description="The best documentation doesn't just inform—it transforms confusion into confidence, complexity into clarity, and hesitation into action."
        ariaLabel="Spark 'aha' moments"
      />

      <Card
        icon="🤝"
        title="I code. I design. I connect."
        description="Great developer experience happens at the intersection of technical accuracy, visual design, and human psychology. I work in all three spaces."
        ariaLabel="I code. I design. I connect."
      />

      <Card
        icon="🚀"
        title="Reduce friction, increase flow"
        description="Every tool I build and every guide I write has one goal: help developers get from question to solution as smoothly as possible."
        ariaLabel="Reduce friction, increase flow"
      />
    </Grid>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Beyond the Code">
    <p>
      When I'm not crafting documentation or building developer tools, you'll find me exploring the
      latest in web technology, contributing to open-source projects, or mentoring aspiring
      technical writers. I'm energized by teaching and lifting others through shared knowledge.
    </p>
    <p>
      Based in the Austin, Texas metropolitan area, I thrive in remote team environments and have
      been successfully working remotely for 5+ years. I believe the best developer experiences are
      built through diverse, distributed teams that bring different perspectives to solving complex
      problems.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Let's Build Better Developer Experiences Together">
    <p>
      Whether you're looking to improve your documentation, build better developer tools, or create
      clearer technical communication, I'd love to hear about your challenges and explore how we
      might work together.
    </p>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* About page styles */
  .intro-section {
    display: flex;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .intro-content {
    flex: 2;
    min-width: 0; /* Allows text to wrap properly */
  }

  .intro-content .lead {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .intro-image {
    flex: 1;
    max-width: 280px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .intro-image img {
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 2px solid var(--border-primary);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px var(--shadow-secondary);
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .intro-text {
    flex: 1;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .intro-content {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 24px;
    }

    .intro-text {
      text-align: left;
    }

    .intro-image img {
      width: 280px;
      height: auto;
    }
  }

  .journey-section,
  .philosophy-section,
  .expertise-section,
  .recognition-section,
  .personal-section,
  .cta-section {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .journey-section h2,
  .philosophy-section h2,
  .expertise-section h2,
  .recognition-section h2,
  .personal-section h2,
  .cta-section h2 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-primary);
    padding-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .career-timeline {
    /* Clean timeline container - no left padding or borders needed */
  }

  .timeline-entry {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 2px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.4);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .timeline-entry.current {
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-primary);
    background: var(--bg-card);
  }

  /* Timeline dots and left-side elements removed - periods now appear above content */

  .timeline-period {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    padding: 8px 12px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-primary);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px var(--shadow-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    text-align: center;
    min-width: 90px;
  }

  .timeline-content h3 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 8px 0;
    font-size: 1.375rem;
  }

  .timeline-content h4 {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    margin: 0 0 16px 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .timeline-content p {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .timeline-content p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Grid styles now handled globally in theme.css */

  .philosophy-item {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 2px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.4);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px;
    text-align: center;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .philosophy-item h3 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 12px 0;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .philosophy-item p {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-weight: 400;
    flex-grow: 1;
  }

  /* Recognition items - ensure equal heights */
  .recognition-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .recognition-item p {
    flex-grow: 1;
  }

  /* Expertise items - ensure equal heights */
  .expertise-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .expertise-item p {
    flex-grow: 1;
  }

  /* Expertise grid styling moved above with other grids */

  .item {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 2px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.4);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .expertise-category h3 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 16px 0;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .expertise-category ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .expertise-category li {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    padding-left: 16px;
    position: relative;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .expertise-category li::before {
    content: '▸';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  .recognition-item {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 2px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.4);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    /* Page load animation */
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(20px);
    animation: slideInUp 400ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1) forwards;
  }

  .recognition-item h3 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 12px 0;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .recognition-item p {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  /* Staggered animation delays */
  .recognition-item:nth-child(1) {
    animation-delay: 100ms;
  }

  .recognition-item:nth-child(2) {
    animation-delay: 200ms;
  }

  .recognition-item:nth-child(3) {
    animation-delay: 300ms;
  }

  .recognition-item:nth-child(4) {
    animation-delay: 400ms;
  }

  .personal-section p,
  .cta-section p {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .personal-section p:last-child,
  .cta-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    /* Mobile intro section - stack vertically */
    .intro-section {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 2rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .intro-image {
      max-width: 240px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .intro-content .lead {
      font-size: 1rem;
      text-align: left;
    }

    /* Mobile timeline - no left padding/margins needed */
    .timeline-period {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      padding: 6px 10px;
      min-width: 80px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    /* Grid responsiveness now handled globally in theme.css */
  }

  /* Job meta styling for journey cards - now using unified .meta class */
</style>
